Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the second annual International Trade Dinner in London, emphasizing the strong relationship between the United States and the United Kingdom. Pence conveyed President Donald Trump's support for the UK's decision to leave the European Union and expressed the US's readiness to negotiate a free trade agreement with the UK after Brexit. Pence highlighted the booming American economy and the potential for increased trade between the two countries. He also emphasized the historical bond between the US and the UK, particularly in the face of shared challenges such as World War II and the Cold War. Pence concluded by expressing his belief that the US and the UK will lead the world to prosperity and peace in the 21st century.